					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You're using the NESAsm assembler, right?  I'm not sure how to include the extra CHR banks in there.  But you could always copy the extra ones on after assembly, with a command like "copy /b file.nes+file1.chr+file2.chr+file3.chr game.nes"
<br />
<br />Also, when you use mapper 3 (and some of the other simple mappers) on a cart, you have to use special way to write to ROM because of bus conflicts.  The value you write has to be in ROM.
<br />
<br />Here's the clearest way to do it:
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">banktable: .byte 0,1,2,3<br /><br />&nbsp;lda #2 ; bank to select<br />&nbsp;tax<br />&nbsp;sta banktable,x<br /></div><br /><br />And a quicker way:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">banktemp:<br />&nbsp;lda #2<br />&nbsp;sta banktemp+1<br /></div></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

